etymology.description: Depicts a bundle of twenty sticks
etymology.interpretation: The character 卄(卄) (niàn, "twenty") visually resembles a grouping of vertical lines, representing the number 20, similar to tally marks.

examples.chinese: 他的年龄是卄岁(他的年齡是卄歲)。
examples.pinyin: Tā de niánlíng shì niàn suì.

examples.chinese: 班级里有卄位学生(班級裡有卄位學生)，他们都积极参加活动(他們都積極參加活動)。
examples.pinyin: Bānjí lǐ yǒu niàn wèi xuéshēng, tāmen dōu jījí cānjiā huódòng.
examples.english: There are twenty students in the class, and they all participate actively in activities.
